{
  "texts": [
    "Their method was trained with a densely connected CNN architecture called FaceLFnet, based on the horizontal and vertical EPIs of light field images.",
    "The authors reported that this method was robust to changes in pose, facial expression, and lighting in face reconstruction tasks.",
    "Unlike single-view face reconstruction methods, multi-view methods do not require strong inductive biases to accomplish model deformation.",
    "These approaches can extract facial features from multiple viewpoints in different images to create more detailed 3D models.",
    "The efficient fusing of features from multiple views is the key to achieving accurate depth estimation and facial texture recovery."
  ]
}